==English==

===Etymology===
Named for the alkaline silicate composition.

===Noun===
'''sodalite'''
# {{mineralogy}} A [[mineral]] of alkaline [[igneous]] and [[plutonic]] [[rock]]s that are low in [[silica]].  Pink sodalite is sometimes called ''hackmanite''.  Sodalite and [[lazurite]] form the ''sodalite Group'' of silicate minerals.

*Chemical composition: Sodium aluminum silicate with chlorine, <math>Na_4Al_3Si_3O_{12}Cl</math>
 
